<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Our business</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
North America Treasury Operations (NTO) provides a range of treasury products and services to clients within the U.S. and Canada. These products and services allow corporate treasurers to manage working capital within their organizations. While much of NTO supports Global Treasury Services (GTS) clients, there are business units such as Wire Transfer Services that support all customer segments across the company.
<br><br>
North America Treasury Operations is organized into several major business units, with responsibilities as follows:
</p>
<ul>
	<li><b>Wire Transfer Operations</b> processing and providing customer service for incoming and outgoing domestic and international U.S. dollar and foreign currency funds transfers for corporate, customer and financial clients worldwide</li>
	<li><b>Trade Operations</b> issuing, processing and providing customer service for Commercial and Standby Letters of Credit, Bankers' Acceptances and Documentary Collections</li>
	<li><b>Libris Government Operations</b> encompasses 3 lines of business that support IRS tax processing, General Lockbox for Federal government agencies and specialty processing for high-volume customers</li>
	<li><b>Global Banknote Operations</b> fulfills requests for foreign currency for wholesale clients based on contracts received from the Wholesale Banknote advisory desks. Bank of America is one of the world's leading providers of global banknote services to financial institutions, and remains the largest provider of wholesale foreign currency to financial institutions in North America</li>
	<li><b>Escrow Management Services</b> a new Bank of America Treasury Management product designed to track, maintain and report balances for clients' customer escrow accounts</li>
	<li><b>Payment Services</b> consists of 5 business units that provide commission disbursement payment and reporting services for the travel industry, payment and settlement services for the healthcare industry and back office accounting and data settlement for the airline industry. The 5 business units are Global Commission Payments, Travel Payment System, Healthcare Payments, InControl and ATCAN.</li>
	<li><b>Trading Support Services</b> consists of 3 business units: Account Analysis, Commercial Treasury operations and Deposit Services</li>
	<li><b>Customer Service and Implementation</b> provides support to our clients and business partners regarding inquiries/investigations and any issues effecting their payment needs and requirements</li>
	<li><b>Operations Risk Management</b> assumes primary accountability for ensuring that effective systems of internal control and compliance are in place throughout the company, and validates the integrity of those controls through a broad and comprehensive monitoring program that meets, and often exceeds, corporate standards</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Overview</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
This unique, 2-year program allows analysts to rotate through our North America Treasury Operations. The program offers exposure to many different areas within North America Treasury Operations and provides a better understanding of where analysts' skills would be best utilized. Analysts will participate in 3 8-month rotations within North America Treasury Operations.
</p>

